      • insert

        public void insert(int ID)
        Adds a node before the current node

        There are three (3) possibilities for inserting a node 1) The current sequence is empty 2) The sequence is non-empty and the current node is at the beginning of the sequence 3) The sequence is non-empty and the current node is not at the beginning of the sequence

        Parameters:
        ID - The integer that will be used as content for the inserted node

      • attach

        public void attach(int ID)
        Adds a node after the current node

        There are three (3) possibilities for inserting a node 1) The current sequence is empty 2) The sequence is non-empty and the current node is at the end of the sequence 3) The sequence is non-empty and the current node is not at the end of the sequence

        Parameters:
        ID - The integer which will be the content for the inserted node

      • append

        public void append(int ID)
        Adds a node to the end of the sequence

        If the head is null (the sequence is empty) then add the new node as the head else use a pointer to traverse the sequence until a node without a next value appears this is the end of the current sequence so append will assign this node's next value to the inserted node the inserted node's prev value becomes the aforementioned node

        Parameters:
        ID - The integer which will be used as the content for the inserted node

      • deleteCurrent

        public void deleteCurrent()
        Deletes the Node that is pointed to by the current pointer

        There are five (5) options as to what the current Node could be 1) A null value 2) A singularity 3) The head node 4) The tail node 5) Some node in the middle of the sequence

      • getSize

        public int getSize()
        Returns the number of elements contained within the sequence

        Determines the size by using starting from the head node and incrementing the int variable, size, until it reaches a null value, then returns the size

        Returns:
        the size of the sequence object

      • combineSequence

        public static Sequence combineSequence(Sequence s1,
                                       Sequence s2)
        Combines two sequences and returns the combination as a new sequence

        Takes the end node in sequence 1 and sets the next pointer to the head node of sequence 2 Takes the head node of sequence 1 and sets the tail pointer to the end node of sequence 1 Returns the new sequence

        Parameters:
        s1 - sequence which will be at the front of the new sequence
        s2 - sequence which will be at the end of the new sequence
        Returns:
        a sequence that is the combination of s2 appended to the end of s1

        Takes the end node of this sequence and sets the next pointer to the head of s1 Takes the head node of s1 and sets the prev pointer to the end of this sequence

        Parameters:
        s1 - sequence which will be appended to this sequence
